;; =============================================================================
;; Spec: Behavioral Verification in the Monitor Phase
;; =============================================================================
;;
;; Design question resolved 2026-04-03:
;;   Where should behavioral verification (orchestrate → observe → policy) run?
;;   Answer: post-PR, during the monitor/observe phase — not pre-PR.
;;
;; Rationale:
;;   - The verify phase is a thin shell around `bb test`: fast, structural,
;;     unit-test correctness only. That bar is sufficient for PR creation.
;;   - Real verification is: run the application, listen to the event stream,
;;     and apply policy to the observed telemetry to determine pass/fail.
;;   - Behavioral runs can be slow (minutes to hours). Blocking PR creation on
;;     them defeats the purpose of a parallel review pipeline.
;;   - The monitor phase is already the "watch and wait" phase. Behavioral
;;     telemetry is another signal stream it should listen to.
;;   - Human reviewers see code AND behavioral verification results together,
;;     giving them richer context at decision time.
;;   - The monitor's redirect loop is already wired to push back to :implement
;;     on CI failure. Behavioral gate failure is the same failure mode.
;;
;; Verification model (three steps):
;;   1. Orchestrate — run the workflow or trigger the behavior under test
;;   2. Observe     — listen to the event stream as execution runs
;;   3. Policy      — apply gate criteria to observed telemetry → pass/fail
;;
;; This mirrors the existing gate/observer/policy-pack architecture:
;;   policy is applied to telemetry, not to subprocess stdout or exit codes.
;;
;; Phase split:
;;   :verify  (pre-PR)  — `bb test` structural correctness, fast
;;   :monitor (post-PR) — behavioral orchestration + telemetry + gate evaluation

{:spec/id     "behavioral-verification-monitor-v1"
 :spec/version "0.1.0"
 :spec/created "2026-04-03"
 :spec/status  "design"

 :spec/title
 "Behavioral Verification in the Monitor Phase"

 :spec/description
 "Extend the monitor/observe phase to run behavioral verification after a PR
  is created: orchestrate the implemented workflow against a test harness or
  staging environment, observe the emitted event stream telemetry, and apply
  policy-pack gates to determine pass/fail. Gate failures redirect back to
  :implement via the existing monitor redirect loop. Behavioral results are
  added to the evidence bundle alongside structural (bb test) results."

 :spec/intent
 {:type  :feature
  :scope ["components/workflow/src/ai/miniforge/workflow/observe_phase.clj"
          "components/gate/src/ai/miniforge/gate"
          "components/observer/src/ai/miniforge/observer"
          "components/policy-pack/src/ai/miniforge/policy_pack"
          "components/event-stream/src/ai/miniforge/event_stream"
          "components/evidence-bundle/src/ai/miniforge/evidence_bundle"]}

 :spec/constraints
 ["Verify phase remains a thin shell — no behavioral logic added pre-PR"
  "Behavioral verification is always post-PR; PR creation is not blocked"
  "Observation surface is the event stream — NOT subprocess stdout/exit codes"
  "Policy evaluation uses the existing gate/policy-pack architecture"
  "Behavioral gate failure triggers the same redirect-to-implement path as CI failure"
  "Behavioral evidence is added to the evidence bundle alongside verify metrics"
  "The spec may declare :spec/behavioral-harness to configure what is orchestrated"
  "If no harness is declared, behavioral verification is skipped (not an error)"]

 :context
 {:normative-refs
  ["N2 §7 — Observe phase lifecycle"
   "N6 — Environment promotion pipeline (executor environment model)"
   "N11 — Task capsule isolation"
   "pr-monitor-loop.spec.edn — PR comment resolution (separate concern)"
   "rn-13-success-predicates.spec.edn — success predicate model"
   "rn-15-evaluation-pipeline.spec.edn — evaluation pipeline design"]

  :existing-infrastructure
  ["gate — evaluates named gate criteria against context"
   "observer — subscribes to event stream, projects state"
   "policy-pack — loads and applies structured rule packs"
   "event-stream — append-only, in-process pub/sub with typed events"
   "evidence-bundle — aggregates all phase outputs into a workflow artifact"
   "verify phase — already runs bb test, captures pass/fail + test output"
   "monitor redirect loop — already redirects to :implement on CI failure"]

  :gap
  "No component currently orchestrates the application under test, observes its
   event stream output, and applies policy to determine behavioral pass/fail.
   The verify phase only runs unit tests (subprocess exit code). Real behavioral
   correctness — does the workflow behave as the spec intended? — is unverified."}

 ;; ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
 ;; MILESTONES
 ;; ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

 :plan/milestones

 [{:milestone/id :M0
   :milestone/title "Design captured (this spec)"
   :milestone/status :done
   :milestone/description
   "Record the architectural decision: verify = thin bb-test shell (pre-PR),
    behavioral verification = orchestrate→observe→policy (post-PR, in monitor).
    No implementation yet."}

  {:milestone/id :M1
   :milestone/title "Behavioral harness protocol"
   :milestone/status :todo
   :milestone/description
   "Define the protocol for behavioral harnesses: what a harness must provide,
    how it is declared in a spec, how the monitor phase invokes it.

    A harness is a function or component that:
      - Accepts the executor environment (worktree-path, environment-id)
      - Triggers the application behavior under test
      - Returns a channel or collection of observed events

    Harness types to support:
      :bb-script   — run a Babashka script in the executor environment
      :workflow    — re-run a sub-workflow against a test fixture
      :repl-eval   — evaluate a Clojure form in a REPL against the environment

    Deliverables:
      - Protocol definition in components/observer or new components/harness
      - Spec schema extension: :spec/behavioral-harness {:type :bb-script :path ...}
      - Monitor phase reads :spec/behavioral-harness and invokes harness if present"}

  {:milestone/id :M2
   :milestone/title "Event stream observation during behavioral run"
   :milestone/status :todo
   :milestone/description
   "Wire the monitor phase to collect event stream telemetry during the
    behavioral harness run. The observer subscribes before the harness fires,
    collects all emitted events, and closes the subscription when the harness
    completes (or times out).

    Events of interest:
      - :phase/* — phase transitions, decisions
      - :gate/* — gate evaluations, pass/fail
      - :llm/* — model calls, token usage
      - :error/* — exceptions, failures
      - Application-domain events declared in the spec

    Deliverables:
      - Observer subscription wired into monitor phase behavioral run
      - Telemetry snapshot: all events from harness start to completion
      - Timeout enforcement: harness budget from spec or default (10 min)"}

  {:milestone/id :M3
   :milestone/title "Gate evaluation on observed telemetry"
   :milestone/status :todo
   :milestone/description
   "Apply the policy-pack gate criteria to the collected telemetry snapshot.
    Gate evaluation is the same mechanism used in the verify phase for unit
    tests — the difference is the input: event stream projection vs test output.

    Gate examples for behavioral verification:
      :workflow-completed    — at least one :phase/completed event observed
      :no-unhandled-errors   — no :error/unhandled events in stream
      :all-phases-passed     — every phase gate in the stream shows :passed?
      :latency-within-budget — total duration within spec :budget/ms
      :custom-predicate      — spec-declared Clojure predicate over the events

    Deliverables:
      - Gate evaluators for the standard behavioral gate names above
      - Policy-pack integration: behavioral gates declared in spec map to evaluators
      - Gate results: {:gate/name ... :passed? ... :evidence ...} per gate
      - Overall behavioral verdict: all gates passed? → :passed? true"}

  {:milestone/id :M4
   :milestone/title "Monitor redirect loop on behavioral gate failure"
   :milestone/status :todo
   :milestone/description
   "When behavioral gates fail, redirect back to :implement via the existing
    monitor redirect loop. The redirect carries the gate failure evidence as
    the error context — the implementer can see which behavioral assertion
    failed and why.

    Behavioral gate failure is treated identically to CI failure in the monitor:
      - Emit :monitor/behavioral-gate-failed event
      - Set redirect-to :implement in monitor phase context
      - Attach gate failure evidence to the implement retry prompt
      - Budget decrement applies (behavioral failures count toward total budget)

    Special case: if the harness itself errors (not the app behavior), this is
    a :monitor/harness-error — escalate rather than redirect (not a code bug).

    Deliverables:
      - Monitor phase handles :passed? false from gate evaluator
      - Redirect wired to :implement with evidence
      - Harness error vs gate failure distinguished in event types"}

  {:milestone/id :M5
   :milestone/title "Behavioral evidence in the evidence bundle"
   :milestone/status :todo
   :milestone/description
   "Add :evidence/behavioral-verification to the workflow evidence bundle.
    This complements :evidence/verify (unit test results) with behavioral results.

    Schema:
      {:harness/type    keyword
       :harness/path    string
       :gates           [{:gate/name keyword :passed? boolean :evidence map}]
       :passed?         boolean
       :event-count     int
       :duration-ms     long
       :telemetry-snapshot [event]}  ;; trimmed to relevant events only

    Deliverables:
      - evidence-bundle schema extended with :behavioral-verification key
      - Monitor phase writes evidence after gate evaluation
      - Evidence visible in TUI evidence view and web dashboard"}]

