 ;; ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
 ;; OPEN QUESTIONS
 ;; ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

 :open-questions

 [{:q "For specs without a declared harness, should we infer one (e.g., run
       the default workflow entry point against the PR's changes in a sandbox)?
       Or is no-harness always a skip?"
   :lean "Skip — requiring explicit harness declaration avoids surprise runs.
          Implicit orchestration of unknown workflows is too risky."}

  {:q "Should behavioral gate failure create a new commit addressing the
       failure, or should the implementer start from the existing PR branch?"
   :lean "Existing PR branch — amend the implementation in place rather than
          creating a second PR. Keeps the review history coherent."}

  {:q "How do we prevent behavioral runs from being unbounded in cost?
       Who pays for the orchestration?"
   :lean "Enforce a harness budget (tokens + wall time) from the spec.
          Default: 10 min / 5k tokens. Overrun → harness-error, not gate-failure."}]}
